
HTML5, the fifth revision of the HTML standard, introduced several new features and enhancements to improve the functionality and flexibility of web development. Here's a list of some key features of HTML5:

1-Semantic Elements:
<header>, <footer>, <nav>, <article>, <section>, <figure>, <figcaption>, <aside>, etc., provide a more meaningful structure to web documents.

2-Multimedia Elements:
<audio> and <video> elements for embedding media content without the need for third-party plugins.

3-Canvas Element:
<canvas> allows dynamic rendering of graphics and images directly within the browser, enabling the creation of interactive games, charts, and visualizations.

4-SVG (Scalable Vector Graphics):
Support for vector graphics using SVG, providing a way to create resolution-independent graphics and animations.

5-Form Controls:
New input types like email, url, tel, number, date, and range for improved user input handling.
The <datalist> element allows pre-defined options for form controls.

6-Local Storage:
The localStorage and sessionStorage APIs enable storing key-value pairs on the client side, providing a way to persist data between page reloads.

7-Web Storage:
The localStorage and sessionStorage APIs enable storing key-value pairs on the client side, providing a way to persist data between page reloads.

8-Web Workers:
Introduces the ability to run scripts in the background, allowing for concurrent processing and better performance.

8-WebSockets:
Provides a full-duplex communication channel over a single, long-lived connection, enabling real-time data transfer between clients and servers.
